definition.value: Abnormally elevated concentration of a purine compound. Purine compounds are aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a purine moiety, which is formed a pyrimidine-ring ring fused to an imidazole ring.

Abnormally reduced concentration of a purine compound. Purine compounds are aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a purine moiety, which is formed a pyrimidine-ring ring fused to an imidazole ring.
Abnormally diminished level of attention, responsiveness, or wakefulness.
Inflammation of the alimentary part of the gastrointestinal system.
A deficiency in the intake of energy and nutrients.

label.value: Abnormality of the sense of smell

definition.value: An anomaly in the ability to perceive and distinguish scents (odors).
